## Phase 0 — Scaffold & Environment

- [ ] Create NX workspace or clone team repo
- [ ] Create `.env` in workspace root:
  ```
  VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSyBpaG8AF8jQ9GKnwIysXB0xgekW2clUiQ0
  ```
- [ ] Verify `.gitignore` includes `.env`
- [ ] Check `app.tsx` has `isDemo: !apiKey` (false when key exists)
- [ ] Run `npx nx serve game-engine-host --port 4200`
- [ ] Verify no "Preview Mode" banner

**Done when:** App loads, no preview mode banner, DevTools console shows no 401

---

## Phase 1 — Types + Gemini Service

- [ ] Define all TypeScript types in `libs/shared/types`
- [ ] Update `claude.service.ts` to use Gemini:
  - URL: `gemini-1.5-pro:generateContent?key=${apiKey}`
  - No Authorization header — key in URL only
  - Response: `data.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text`
- [ ] Build and verify: `npx nx build claude`

**Done when:** `npx nx build claude` passes with no errors

---

## Phase 2 — Generation Logic (5 rounds)

- [ ] Write `BLACK_BOX_SYSTEM_PROMPT` — forces JSON-only output
- [ ] Write `buildBlackboxPrompt()` — truncates to 4000 chars
- [ ] Write `cleanAndParseResponse()` — strips markdown, extracts JSON
- [ ] Validate: 5 rounds, 6 clues each
- [ ] Retry logic: 2 retries, 1s/2s backoff
- [ ] Test manually: paste text, verify 5 rounds generated

**Done when:** Pasting text generates exactly 5 rounds with 6 clues each

---

## Phase 3 — Game State Hook

- [ ] `useBlackBoxGame` manages:
  - `phase`: start → loading → round_active → round_result → game_complete
  - `currentRoundIndex`: 0–4
  - `currentClueIndex`: 1–6
  - `potentialScore`: updates on next clue
  - `hintAvailable`: true per round
- [ ] `revealNextClue()`: increment index, update score
- [ ] `submitGuess()`: validate, update round state
- [ ] `nextRound()`: if index < 4 → next round, else → game_complete
- [ ] `useHint()`: mark used, deduct 100
- [ ] Save to sessionStorage on every state change

**Done when:** Full game flow works with mock data in console

